	abstract = {Description: In an era of artificial intelligence (AI), the promise of technological advancement must be balanced with the protection of human values. As AI systems become integrated into critical areas like law enforcement, healthcare, employment, and education, concerns over bias, surveillance, accountability, and discrimination increase. Safeguarding social justice and human rights requires ethical innovation and robust legal and policy frameworks that ensure transparency, fairness, and inclusivity. Further exploration may ensure these machines serve equitably and uphold individual dignity and rights. Safeguarding Social Justice and Human Rights in the Age of AI examines the multifaceted relationship between societal change and AI. It explores how technological progress might be used to improve human welfare. This book covers topics such as ecology, global business, and smart cities, and is a useful resource for sociologists, policymakers, engineers, business owners, academicians, researchers, and scientists. Coverage: The many academic areas covered in this publication include, but are not limited to: • Artificial Intelligence • Democratic Systems • Digital Surveillance • Ecology • Gender Studies • Global Business • Government and Law • Human Rights • International Relations • Policymaking • Smart Cities • Social Entrepreneurship • Social Justice • Sustainable Development © 2026 by IGI Global Scientific Publishing.},
